In the United States of America (USA), reliability is the determinant of service quality as it is 
the heart of service. However, for the purpose of this study, unreli ability refers to poor 
service; despite all other attributes, the customers regard the organisation as incompetent and 
switch to another service provider if the service is not performed reliably.  Macharia (2014: 
17) agreed that reliability is the most cha llenging factor for all service organisations, since it 
is an outcome measure by which customers judge every service experience. Moreover, 
service delivery gives companies the chance to delight customers by exceeding their 
expectations, leading to positive  perceptions of service quality. Even though customer 
retention is seen as the various behavioural consequences of service quality, it produces a 
direct impact on the market share of the organisation (Lee, 2002: 244). 
 
